<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<html xmlns:MadCap="http://www.madcapsoftware.com/Schemas/MadCap.xsd">
    <body>
        <p>Just-In-Time (JIT) provisioning enables automatic user account creation in <MadCap:variable name="okta-variables.ProductName" /> the first time a user authenticates with Active Directory (AD) delegated authentication or Desktop SSO.</p>
        <p>JIT account creation and activation only works for  users who are not already <MadCap:variable name="okta-variables.ProductName" /> users.  This means that users who are confirmed on the import results page, regardless of whether or not they were subsequently activated, are not eligible for JIT activation. When JIT is enabled, users do not receive activation emails.</p>
        <p>For JIT provisioning, delegated authentication must be enabled. If delegated authentication is not enabled, <MadCap:variable name="okta-variables.ProductName" /> user accounts can only be created using bulk import.</p>
        <p>When JIT is enabled for your org and delegated authentication is selected for your AD, JIT is used to create user profiles and import user data. The username format is used to authenticate AD sourced users. If you use a custom expression to format the <MadCap:variable name="okta-variables.ProductName" /> username, the last selected and saved non-custom username is used for authentication. The UPN is the default, non-custom username.</p>
        <p>For a list of known issues, see <MadCap:xref href="../../Topics/Directory/ad-agent-known-issues.htm">Active Directory integration known issues</MadCap:xref>.</p>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <MadCap:snippetText src="task steps/Directory_DirectoryIntegrations.flsnp" />
            </li>
            <li>Click <span class="uicontrol">Active Directory</span>  and then click the <span class="uicontrol">Provisioning</span> tab.</li>
            <li>Click <span class="uicontrol">To Okta</span> in the <span class="uicontrol">Settings</span>&#160;list.</li>
            <li>Click <span class="uicontrol">Edit</span> in the <span class="uicontrol">General</span> area.</li>
            <li>Select the <span class="uicontrol">Create and update users on login</span> check box next to <span class="uicontrol">JIT&#160;provisioning</span>.</li>
            <li>
                <MadCap:snippetText src="task steps/Click_Save.flsnp" />
            </li>
        </ol>
    </body>
</html>